      "label": "Further remarks",
      "value": "The handwriting on the verso is different from the recto and the texts are unrelated."
    },
    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "Recto: Familiar greeting formulae open and end the letter (l. 1; 11-12). The sender and addressee seem to be connected through some kind of commercial relationship. The sender informs the addressee that he has said something to a third person (l. 5). He asks the addressee for his opinion concerning something with the formula usually employed for polite request (l. 7). He finally urges him to calculate someone's bill (l. 8) and asks him to order or inform a third person about what he wrote the addressee (l. 9)."
    },
    {
      "label": "Diacritical dots",
      "value": "There are some diacritical dots and some unconventional ligatures."
    }
